Two factory workers identified as Oyekanmi Abdulkadri (aged 30) and Opeyemi Mustapha (aged 33) have been ordered to be remanded in Corrections for alleged stealing plastics of the company. The two defendants were an employee of Iyanu Plastic Industry was arraigned before an Osun State Magistratesâ€™ Court sitting in Osogbo on two counts of conspiracy and stealing. The Police Prosecutor, Mr Adeoye Kayode informed the presiding magistrate, Mrs Modupe Awodele, that the two defendants Opeyemi (female) and Oyekanmi (male) conspired together to steal plastic of the company which belongs to Fidudusola Fisayo worth N14,800 on January 22, 2022, at Iyanu Plastic Industry, Osogbo where they are working. He noted that the offences contravened sections 516 and 383 of the criminal code Cap 34 Vol. 2, Laws of Osun state of Nigeria, 2002. However, the two defendants pleaded not guilty to the offences preferred against them. The defence counsel, B Y Dauda urged the court to grant bail to the defendants in the most liberal term. The prosecutor opposed the bail application saying that the defendants have been stealing the plastics for a long time. The Magistrate, Mrs Modupe Awodele ordered that they should be remanded and she adjourned the case till February 9, 2021.